PAST MEDICAL HISTORY
1. Sigmoid colon cancer.  Discussed above, no evidence of recurrence.
2. Diabetes mellitus, type-2.  He was diagnosed in approximately 1955.  He has been on insulin for several years now.  He believes his last hemoglobin A1c was 6.7 in October.  His local provider's goal is to have this under 6.  He has problems with hypoglycemia at times, and last evening reported his blood sugar was only 66, and he did not take his Lantus and has not taken insulin yet this morning.  He usually is symptomatic and can feel when he is getting low and is able to correct it and has not had a serious hypoglycemic reaction.  He is not known to have neuropathy or nephropathy but is known to have retinopathy and is followed by an ophthalmologist.
3. Left inguinal hernia.  Discussed above.
4. Coronary artery disease.  This is partially discussed above.  Underwent five-vessel CABG here in 1994.  He has what seems to be significant cardiomyopathy related to his ischemic disease, as it is suspected he had a MI before 1994.  His ejection fraction by the echo, as discussed above, was only 20% prior to his CABG surgery.  He has not had a recent evaluation.  He denies chest pain, palpitations, has not used nitroglycerin and has never been prescribed it.  He has a family history of coronary artery disease with his son who underwent four-vessel bypass at age 45.  Dr. Keith had a carotid ultrasound performed four years ago with no significant stenosis.
5. Retinopathy that is related to his diabetes.
6. History of multiple adenomatous colon polyps.  Discussed above.
7. Hearing loss.  He spontaneously developed complete hearing loss in his right ear.  The etiology is unclear.  He also has diminished hearing and presbycusis in the left ear and wears a hearing aid intermittently in the left ear.
8. Hypertension.  He says his blood pressure is typically under good control.
9. Hyperlipidemia.  He is on Lipitor.  He has been on the 20-mg for many years and believes his cholesterol is well-controlled.
PAST SURGICAL HISTORY
1. Tonsillectomy.
2. Vasectomy.
3. Cholecystectomy with questionable appendectomy in the 1970s.
4. Right inguinal hernia repair without mesh in 1977.
5. Lower anterior resection for sigmoid cancer, 1989, here by Dr. Brent Miller.
6. Five-vessel CABG here, 1994.

